# Sage With You — Supabase (browser). Copy to ".env" and restart `npm run dev`.
# Dashboard: https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/htckswutkpktxclyijwk

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://htckswutkpktxclyijwk.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=paste_anon_public_key_here

# Public site URL for Open Graph / canonical (no trailing slash). Production: https://sage-with-you.org
# VITE_SITE_URL=https://sage-with-you.org
# (Keep default og:image URLs in index.html aligned with this host, or regenerate defaults after deploy.)

# Library files (Supabase Storage): run migration 003_library_storage_bucket.sql, upload objects under bucket "library"
# (pdfs/1.pdf … pdfs/15.pdf, videos/4.mp4 & 12.mp4, articles/7.html … 14.html), then enable:
# VITE_LIBRARY_USE_STORAGE=true   (local .env uses this for Storage URL + existence checks)
# Optional override: VITE_LIBRARY_BUCKET=library

# After first deploy, add your production site URL under:
# Authentication → URL Configuration → Redirect URLs
# (include http://localhost:5173 for local dev and /reset-password path as needed)

# Contact form: run supabase/migrations/001_contact_submissions.sql then 002_contact_submissions_edge_only.sql
# in the SQL Editor (002 after deploying Edge Function `submit-contact`).
#
# Production checklist (Supabase Dashboard → Edge Functions → Secrets):
#   submit-contact: CONTACT_SMTP_USER, CONTACT_SMTP_PASS, CONTACT_SMTP_FROM (optional: HOST, PORT, BCC)
#   submit-contact rate limit: run migration 004_contact_submit_rate_limit.sql, then set CONTACT_RATE_SALT (secret string)
#     optional CONTACT_RATE_LIMIT_PER_HOUR (default 25)
#   delete-account: SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY is injected by Supabase; ensure function is deployed
#
# O365 mail for confirmations: set Edge secrets CONTACT_SMTP_* in Supabase (not in this file).
# See supabase/functions/submit-contact/index.ts
#
# Edge Functions: run deploy-supabase-functions.bat (Windows) or ./deploy-supabase-functions.sh (Mac/Linux)
# from this folder after `supabase login`. Optional: SAGE_WITH_YOU_PROJECT_REF=your_ref
